Former Public Enterprises Minister, Lynne Brown continues her testimony at the state capture inquiry. JOHANNESBURG - Former Public Enterprises Minister, Lynne Brown is expected to continue testifying at the State Capture Inquiry on Monday morning. Brown will be delivering more evidence about Eskom. WATCH: Lynne Brown denies alleged links to Guptas On Friday, she denied allegations of wrongdoing, and that the Guptas influenced her choice of board members for the power utility. Brown told the commission that she lives a modest life and that her family suffered because of allegations that she was one of the architects of state capture.